\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This is the {\b DEVELOPMENT} version from GitHub. It may contain experimental features or bugs. For the stable version, please use the official ReaPack/ReaTeam repositories.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Quad Cortex MIDI control\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Real-time MIDI control for Neural DSP Quad Cortex via Reaper Regions.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Automates Presets using "#BankLetter" (e.g., #1A).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Automates Scenes using "!Sx" (e.g., !S1 or !SA).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Auto-activates Gig View on Play and Tuner on Stop (both can be toggled).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b MIDI Clock Support}: Reaper will send tempo/clock to the Quad Cortex if "Send clock" is enabled for your MIDI output in Reaper's Preferences.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 USAGE INSTRUCTIONS\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab AUTOMATIC INSTALLATION & SETUP\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Run this script. If it's the first time, the SETUP WIZARD will open.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab The script AUTOMATICALLY creates a dedicated MIDI track (Default: "Quad Cortex MIDI control").\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab This track is pre-configured: Armed, Monitoring ON, and Record DISABLED (Mode 2).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab In the Wizard, select the correct MIDI Hardware Output ID for your QC.\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab TEMPO & MIDI CLOCK SYNC\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab To sync Tempo (BPM) to your QC:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Preferences > MIDI Devices > Double-click Output > Check "Send clock to this device".\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab SYNC YOUR PRESETS AND SCENES\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab PRESETS: Use "#BankLetter" format (e.g., "#1A", "#12C").\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab SCENES: Use "!SA" to "!SH" (Matches QC Footswitches A to H).\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab LOG LEVELS\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Log Level 1 [INFO]: Preset/Scene changes and Transport status.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Log Level 2 [DEBUG]: Full configuration details and file operations.\sa180\sa180\par}
}
